text.section:
This section does not apply to:
reinsurance;
life insurance, health insurance, or annuity contracts;
insurance of:
rolling stock, vessels, or aircraft of a common carrier used in interstate or foreign commerce;
a vehicle principally garaged and used outside the State; or
liability or other risks, incident to the ownership, maintenance, or operation of a subject of insurance under item (i) or (ii) of this item;
insurance of property while transported in interstate or in foreign trade, or any liability or risk incident to the transportation;
insurance of wet marine and transportation risks;
bid bonds issued in connection with public or private contracts;
policies or endorsements issued through:
insurance producers compensated only by salary;
insurers not using insurance producers in the general solicitation of business;
mutual insurers or other insurers not customarily using insurance producers compensated by commission if no commission is payable to an insurance producer on the policy or endorsement; or
insurers or groups of insurers under common management or control that are represented exclusively by insurance producers who represent only the insurers or groups of insurers;
reciprocal insurers; or
insurance written through:
the Maryland Automobile Insurance Fund; or
the Maryland Property Insurance Availability Program.

section.section:
A person may not sign or countersign a policy or endorsement subject to this section unless the person:
is a licensed insurance producer;
is a resident of this State;
is compensated by commissions on policies subject to this section; and
is not an employee or officer of the insurer issuing the policy.
